      ],
      "content": "Use the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[wit_firstref](../Token/wit_firstref_md.md)]</ph><bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Android general configuration policy<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> to configure settings for:"
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        427,
        580
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Mobile device security settings<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> – Choose from a list of predefined settings that let you control a range of features and functionality on the device."
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Kiosk mode<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> (for Samsung KNOX devices only) - Lock a device to only allow certain features to work.",
      "pos": [
        586,
        688
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, you can allow a device to only run one managed app that you specify, or you can disable the volume buttons on a device.",
      "pos": [
        689,
        821
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "These settings might be used for a demonstration model of a device, or a device that is dedicated to performing only one function, such as a point of sale device.",
      "pos": [
        822,
        984
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Compliant and noncompliant apps<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> - Specify a list of apps that are compliant, or not compliant in your company.",
      "pos": [
        990,
        1104
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "On Android and iOS devices, the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Noncompliant Apps Report<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> can be used to view the compliance of apps you specified in the list against the apps that users have installed (but cannot actually block the installation of the app).",
      "pos": [
        1105,
        1334
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        1338,
        1896
      ],
      "content": "[!TIP]\nYou can configure terms and conditions for users to ensure that they acknowledge that apps on their device, including personal apps will be evaluated, and noncompliant apps will either be blocked, or reported as noncompliant. Users must accept these terms and conditions before they can enroll their device and use the company portal to get apps. For more information about using terms and conditions, see [Working with terms and conditions policies in Microsoft Intune](http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ce59fb93-01fd-4822-a57d-45ca7d89843d).",
      "leadings": [
        "",
        "> "
      ],
      "nodes": [
